task: Move the robot arm to three positions forming a triangle.

results.output:
# Define the triangle vertices in meters
point1 = (0.5, 0.0, 0.1)  # Vertex 1 (x, y, z)
point2 = (0.0, 0.5, 0.1)  # Vertex 2 (x, y, z)
point3 = (-0.5, 0.0, 0.1) # Vertex 3 (x, y, z)

# Set default orientation as a neutral pose (pointing downwards)
qx, qy, qz, qw = 0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0

# Move to the first position
set_end_position(point1[0], point1[1], point1[2], qx, qy, qz, qw)

# Move to the second position
set_end_position(point2[0], point2[1], point2[2], qx, qy, qz, qw)

# Move to the third position
set_end_position(point3[0], point3[1], point3[2], qx, qy, qz, qw)
